📘 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟖 – 𝐋𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧 𝐆𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐀𝟏 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐌𝐞: 𝐆𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐒𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞

Today, let’s explore basic German sentence structure and how questions work.



✅ 𝐁𝐚𝐬𝐢𝐜 𝐒𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐑𝐮𝐥𝐞𝐬:

The subject conjugates the verb.

 👉 Ich lerne. (I learn.)

The verb is mostly in the second position.

 👉 Ich lerne Deutsch. (I am learning German.)

 👉 Heute gehe ich ins Kino. (Today, I am going to the cinema.)



❓ 𝐐𝐮𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞𝐬:

▶️ 𝐖-𝐅𝐫𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐧 (W-Questions)

Questions beginning with W-words like Was (What), Wo (Where), Wie (How), etc.

🗣️ Here, the verb is in the second place:

Wie heißt du? (What is your name?)

Wo wohnst du? (Where do you live?)

Was machst du? (What are you doing?)

Wann kommst du? (When are you coming?)

Warum lernst du Deutsch? (Why are you learning German?)



▶️ 𝐉𝐚/𝐍𝐞𝐢𝐧-𝐅𝐫𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐧 (Yes/No Questions)

These start with the verb.

🗣️ Here, the verb is in the first place:

Kommst du aus Indien? (Are you from India?)

Lernst du Deutsch? (Are you learning German?)

Magst du Kaffee? (Do you like coffee?)

Hast du Geschwister? (Do you have siblings?)

Bist du Student? (Are you a student?)



✍️ 𝐏𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐓𝐢𝐩:

Pick any verb (like lesen = to read) and form 3 sentence types:

📌 Statement: Ich lese ein Buch.

 📌 W-Question: Was liest du?

 📌 Ja/Nein Question: Liest du ein Buch?



Let’s keep building your German, one sentence at a time. 🌱



 ✨ Share your own sentence in the comments if you’d like me to review it!

